Does the regex for 4chanx not support groups or something? That would be way cleaner if you do this:
>/[b8][l1]([a4*]ck|[e3][a4*]ch)[e3]d/i;boards:trash

Also since you're using //i (case insensitive), you don't need to differentiate between lowercase and uppercase. "k" is the same as "K".
Plus you have a lot of unnecessary groups from the look of it. You don't need to put everything in groups in order to use the OR gate. It's fine if you do it like /this|or|that/
If I were to make the above example more readable, it's basically:
>/bl(ack|each)ed/i
